            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sanford</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 12, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch dated July 3 (No. 11) has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>I am quite content, under existing circumstances, with the disposition you
                    propose in that paper to make of the subject of passports, and I acquiesce very
                    cheerfully in the views which you take of the importance of vigilance in regard
                    to the movements of disaffected citizens of our own country travelling in
                    Europe.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c., Brussels.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
